description.narrative:
In Burkina Faso the current referential in terms of development is the Strategy of Accelerated Growth for Sustainable Development (SCADD).Burkina Faso is entering its second phase of implementation of this policy, after mixed results during the first phase. The project aims to monitor the second phase specifically in the areas of health, education, water and employment to improve the socioeconomic conditions of the population.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&bull; In the area of ​​health, the reception of patients will be referred problematic.
&nbsp;
&bull; In the area of ​​education, the effectiveness of the partnership between government and the private sector is the problem to be studied.
&nbsp;
&bull; With regard to water and sanitation, the availability of infrastructure will be targeted.
&nbsp;
&bull; For youth employment, the mechanisms for assisting job search will be problematic to touch.
&nbsp;
The project objectives will be pursued through the activities described herein.
&nbsp;
&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design of data collection tools. This activity will serve as an extension to the contribution of civil society to guide development reports prepared during the 2011-2013 three-year plan by the CDCAP. It will operationalize tools for collecting data on areas chosen so that the CSB and other local and national actors to consolidate the information needed to track citizen priorities SCADD.
&nbsp;
&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appropriating meeting tools. This meeting will bring together stakeholders to be accountable for data collection and advocacy to enable them to become familiar with the tools produced. The workshop will serve at the same time enrich the tools available.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data collection. This activity will be carried out by the CSB mainly at local level and focus on priority areas of SCADD selected for citizen monitoring.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Centralization, data processing and preparation of the report. This step will be to gather all the data collected in the process and develop the monitoring report that will be placed in the section of the CPR already designed by CDCAP in the 2011 three-year plan - 2013.
&nbsp;
&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dissemination of the report. This will be achieved through a workshop or other publicized in order to disseminate the report and its results. Broadcast channels already in place such as CDCAP website will be utilized to bring the information to the public on the work and results of CDCAP.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participation in dialogue frameworks (advocacy). This activity remains one of the most important CDCAP. It is organizing advocacy within the existing dialogue frameworks in areas where the CSB involved in the project are, and running regularly. The data collected at local and national level and who helped draft the national report (CPR) will be the basis of the plea based on reliable and verifiable information.
&nbsp;
The dialogues executives targeted are primarily those of SCADD occurring nationally (Annual review, mid-term review, specific studies, CSD, etc.) and local (CRD). Sectorial frameworks are also targets for policy advocacy done by the CDCAP.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;The project will be implemented by the Centre de Suivi et d'Analyse Citoyennes des Politiques Publiques. It will affect 15 communes&nbsp;but the results will beficit to all people living in Burkina Faso.
&nbsp;
The target groups is governement and ministries, policy makers and local authorities. The main thematic focus is human right. 
